Male gonopore generally in furrow of XI b5/6, or at anterior part of XI b6 (Figs 9E, 10E). Female gonopore in furrow of XIII a1/a2, located behind gastropore (Figs 9F, 10G). Gonopores separated by six annuli (Figs 9E, 10E). Testisacs multiple, two or three testisacs on each side in each annulus, in XVI b5-XVII b6 to XXIII a1-XXV b6 (Fig. 11A). Paired epididymides in XVI a2/b5-XVII b5 to XVI b5-XVII b6 (Fig. 11A). Ejaculatory bulbs absent. Ejaculatory ducts in XI b5 to XVI a2/b5-XVII b5, loosely coiled, each winding from each junction with epididymis, narrowing at junction with atrial cornu, then turning inward toward atrial cornu without pre-atrial loop (Fig. 11
A-D
). Pair of atrial cornua in XI b5 and b6, undeveloped, coniform (Fig. 11B). Atrium short, muscular, globular in XI b5 and b6 (Fig. 11
B-D
). Ovisacs one pair, thin-walled, globular, in XIII a2 and b5 (Fig. 11A, E). Oviducts thin-walled, right or left oviduct crossing ventrally beneath nerve cord, both oviducts converging into common oviduct in XIII a2 (Fig. 11A, E). Common oviduct thin-walled, short, directly ascending to female gonopore (Fig. 11E).
